value.title: UK PM Johnson says 'resilient' Trump will make strong recovery
value.excerpt: British Prime Minster Boris Johnson said on Saturday he has no doubt U.S. President Donald Trump will make a very strong recovery from COVID-19, calling him a very "resilient character".

value.title: Missouri governor mirrors Trump: Covid-positive after months of virus criticism
value.excerpt: Like the president, Missouri Gov. Mike Parson was under fire for reopening too quickly as he ran for reelection. Then he tested positive for coronavirus.

value.excerpt: The U.S. government knows how to handle an incapacitated commander in chief, but has no idea how to deal with a very sick vice president.

value.title: There will be more space between Pence and Harris at next week's debate
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence and Democratic vice presidential nominee Kamala Harris will be separated by 12 feet at their debate on Wednesday, a source familiar with the plans tells CNN.

value.title: Trump administration puts up billboards of immigration violators in Pennsylvania
value.excerpt: The Trump administration has put up billboards in Pennsylvania of immigration violators, an unprecedented move taken in a swing state a month before the presidential election.

value.title: Biden launches ads touting his faith after cardinal says he's 'not a Catholic in good standing'
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Joe Biden launched an ad campaign seeking to highlight his Catholic faith as many conservatives and fellow Catholics have questioned the sincerity of his beliefs.

value.title: Sanders to host socially distant rally for Biden in New Hampshire
value.excerpt: Bernie Sanders will hold a socially distanced rally for Democratic nominee Joe Biden in New Hampshire on Saturday, the Biden campaign announced.

value.title: Trump team thinks Nevada is in play. Is it?
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign has been hitting Nevada harder than ever this election season, and they seem certain the state might be President Trump’s for the taking this November.

value.title: Host of Pence-Harris VP debate says they still plan on holding event
value.excerpt: The vice presidential debate between Mike Pence and Sen. Kamala Harris is still going on as planned on Wednesday, despite President Trump’s positive Covid-19 test, a debate host spokesperson told Fox News.

value.title: Biden to hit the campaign trail after negative test for COVID-19
value.excerpt: Democratic presidential candidate Joe Biden plans to head to the battleground state of Michigan and resume campaigning on Friday after testing negative for coronavirus, hours after President Donald Trump was sidelined by contracting the virus.

value.title: 'This was avoidable': Trump has been downplaying the virus from the start
value.excerpt: In recent weeks, Trump has put himself and others at risk by holding mass gatherings, some indoors, and shunning mask use while claiming the end of the virus was just around the corner.

value.title: Pelosi: Trump diagnosis 'tragic,' hopefully leads to 'saner approach' to pandemic
value.excerpt: Speaker Nancy Pelosi said that President Trump’s COVID-19 diagnosis is “tragic” and “very sad,” but predictable, given his frequent contact with crowds.

value.title: Melania Trump announces she has 'mild symptoms' of coronavirus
value.excerpt: First lady Melania Trump said Friday that she is experiencing "mild symptoms" but is "looking forward to a speedy recovery" following her Covid-19 diagnosis.
